^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 340 - March 17, 2003^*N
 ^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
I played this week's deal yesterday in the finals of the ^*BJacoby Open Swiss Teams^*N at the ACBL North American Championships in Philadelphia. The bad news is that I misplayed this deal and went down in a slam that I should have made. The good new is that my team won the event despite our result on this deal!

My partner in Philadelphia was ^*BChristal Henner^*N. Christal and I had played a grand total of 12 deals (on ^*BBridge Base Online^*N) before the tournament, but we really hit it off at the table. Besides being a terrific player, Christal is also an excellent partner. I thoroughly enjoyed playing with her.

Christal and 2 of our teammates (^*BPeter Bertheau^*N and ^*BFredrik Nystrom^*N of Sweden) were part of a team that reached the semi-finals of the ^*BRosenblum Cup World Championships^*N last year in Montreal. Our other teammates, Italians ^*BFulvio Fantoni^*N and ^*BClaudio Nunes^*N, had an even bigger result in Montreal - they were the Gold Medalists in the ^*BWorld Open Pairs^*N. 

This was my 3rd win in a North American Championship event, but despite all of their international accomplishments, none of my teammates had ever won a North American Championship before yesterday. As such, our win in the Swiss was especially exciting. This was a great group of people and it was a privilege to be part of their first victory in a major ACBL Championship.

I played on the same team in the ^*BVanderbilt^*N and things were going very smoothly until we had to face the powerful ^*BNickell^*N team in the round of 16. 

|
