^*BNick Nickell^*N-^*BDick Freeman^*N, ^*BJeff Meckstroth^*N-^*BEric Rodwell^*N, and ^*BBob Hamman^*N-^*BPaul Soloway^*N (^*BEric Kokish^*N is their coach) are arguably the strongest bridge team in the world right now. This team was playing in great form against us and they continued to do so for the next several days after they knocked out my team. Eventually the Nickell team won the Vanderbilt. Congratulations!

The entire semi-finals and finals of the Vanderbilt were broadcast live through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N. Every time we do a live vugraph broadcast we set new attendance records on our site. This time there were well over 1400 people logged in at the peak time and over half of these were watching the live broadcast (presumably the other half preferred to play online bridge).

These broadcasts have been very well received and we will be producing presentations of several other major tournaments in the upcoming months. I just got word that a Junior tournament in Sweden will be broadcast through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N on March 22 and 23. When the session starting times are known this information will be posted at:

